<headline>Special Weather Statement issued February 17 at 3:50AM EST  by NWS Grand Rapids</headline>
<description>...Roads to become slick this morning as temperatures fall...
Wet roads first thing this morning could become slick from North to
South as temperatures fall below freezing. In addition, some light
snow on top of it, could add to the slick conditions.
Another concern will be back roads that were snow covered and saw
rain on top of them. Those back roads are likely icy, and will only
become more slick as temperatures fall.
Anyone out on area roads this morning should be watching for wet
roads turning icy quickly as temperatures drop below freezing. Allow
for some extra time to drive to your destination.</description>
